%h3.heading-medium{ id: 'phase-tags'} Alpha and Beta phase tags
%p Phase tags are mostly used inside phase banners as an indication of the state of a project. It’s possible to use them outside phase banners, for example as part of a service header.

%h4.heading-small Alpha tag
.example
  %strong.phase-tag ALPHA
%pre
  %code.language-haml
    :preserve
      %strong.phase-tag ALPHA

%h4.heading-small Beta tag
.example
  %strong.phase-tag BETA

%pre
  %code.language-haml
    :preserve
      %strong.phase-tag BETA

%h3.heading-medium{ id: 'creating-phase-banners'} Creating alpha and beta banners
%p.text Use the GOV.UK Sass phase banner mixin &ndash; find this in the GOV.UK frontend toolkit <a href="https://github.com/alphagov/govuk_frontend_toolkit/blob/master/stylesheets/design-patterns/_alpha-beta.scss">alpha-beta.scss</a> file.

%p.text If you’ve previously used <code class="code">phase-banner-alpha</code> or <code class="code">phase-banner-beta</code> classes in your markup you should change them to <code class="code">phase-banner</code>.

%p <a href="https://designpatterns.hackpad.com/Alpha-and-beta-banners-HpbaBjaYRSJ" rel="external">Discuss alpha and beta banners on the design patterns Hackpad</a>
